{
  "stem": "2004.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that time, we were no longer hungry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As I pointed out, the minute we were liberated, we never saw hunger because if it wasn't the American economy, it was the rations that the Americans brought us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was no longer a matter of bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, it was a matter of getting fruit, which we didn't see for a long time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was candy bars, and chewing gum, and whatever else we could get a hold of, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they were both very kind.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was-- this was again something which we don't forget-- which you don't forget easily.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, being in Italy, we ended up in a place called Santa Maria di Bagno, which was really a fascist resort-- a former fascist resort-- beautifully located right on the ocean.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like-- we, we-- the villas that we got were really abandoned villas-- very primitive, but abandoned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And to they just had bare necessities with the UNRRA or the Jewish Brigade was able to secure for us-- sleeping accommodations and things like that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that time, we already had some clothing change.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We already got some things from the UNRRA, something that we could do with.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Food was no problem.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had enough food because again, we were supplied by both the American and the-- and the Jewish Brigade.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were there for, I would say, from somewhere around maybe July of 1945 until the winter of that same year, 1945.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then it became apparent that getting into Palestine wasn't going to be all that easy because the British closed the immigration.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We heard about cases whereby any ship that came in was turned away because there was problems with the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we decided to look.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
